391
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:27,640
(Caring for her)

392
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,880
But seeing how hard she tried,

393
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,190
that's all that matters.

394
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:35,000
My left hand's here,

395
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:35,590
and then I...

396
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,400
It's normal to lose the ribbon.

397
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:37,830
Yeah.

398
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:38,880
No, it really doesn't.

399
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:40,830
That's not normal.

400
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,000
It was supposed to be...

401
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:43,800
An even chance.

402
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:48,640
You didn't get hurt, huh?

403
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:49,350
No.

404
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,280
Not tiring at all.

405
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,310
Hold this part here.

406
00:19:07,760 --> 00:19:08,950
Get another disposable towel.

407
00:19:13,070 --> 00:19:13,590
Want one?

408
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,160
You wanna lie down?

409
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,950
The "young master" is here.

410
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:25,830
You're totally on vacation.

411
00:19:25,830 --> 00:19:26,640
Yeah, totally.

412
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:32,560
(Pool Competition Final)
Wu Yihan and Yang Tianyu,

413
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:34,920
(Yang & Zhao VS Wu & Yang)
Yang Tinghong and Zhao Enda, get ready.

414
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,760
Only one ribbon for the final.

415
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:40,110
(Just one ribbon)
First to grab it wins.

416
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:40,760
Let's go.

417
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:42,760
Here we go again.

418
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:43,230
Come on.

419
00:19:43,950 --> 00:19:44,640
You're the best.

420
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,430
The best.

421
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:50,830
We're starting?

422
00:19:50,830 --> 00:19:51,400
Yeah.

423
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:53,230
Boys needed?

424
00:19:53,950 --> 00:19:54,920
We should head out.

425
00:19:55,310 --> 00:19:55,830
Alright.

426
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:56,710
Sure.

427
00:19:56,710 --> 00:19:57,190
Let's go.

428
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:58,470
Well, we're off.

429
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:00,160
(Dragged off the battlefield)

430
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,160
Han's got long arms.

431
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,680
She's got a advantage
in grabbing the ribbon.

432
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:04,230
I just need to keep an eye on Enda.

433
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:09,350
That's fierce.

434
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:43,620
(Wu Yihan
takes off the ribbon first and wins)

435
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:52,160
Sis, you're way too good.

436
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,830
Your arms are so long
and you're so tough.

437
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:55,000
How is someone like this

438
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:55,880
even real?

439
00:20:56,470 --> 00:20:57,950
Yang.

440
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,590
Do you need a towel?

441
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:00,520
Yeah, I do.

442
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,350
Here.

443
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:03,950
Put it on, it's a bit damp, be careful.

444
00:21:05,730 --> 00:21:06,430
Losing in the end.

445
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:07,760
Maybe it's really because Han

446
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,590
has such a big physical advantage.

447
00:21:09,590 --> 00:21:10,800
So, nothing we can do about it.

448
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,880
Just let things flow as they may.

449
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,830
Well done.

450
00:21:14,230 --> 00:21:15,030
Are you cold?

451
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,950
Congratulations,
Wu Yihan and Yang Tianyu.

452
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,880
(Wu & Yang win the arrangement)
You two have

453
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,160
the right
to plan the final off-island date.

454
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:33,110
The date selection for tomorrow

455
00:21:33,110 --> 00:21:35,350
will open tonight at Balance Zone.

456
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,230
We can assign people.

457
00:21:37,230 --> 00:21:38,560
Han, you're in charge.

458
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,110
Han.

459
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:40,920
You all gotta suck up to me today.

460
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:42,070
So happy.

461
00:21:42,070 --> 00:21:43,280
Tianyu and I

462
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:44,640
are both super competitive.

463
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:45,950
I just got a free win.

464
00:21:45,950 --> 00:21:48,160
Feels like I always get free wins.

465
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,420
(The luckiest man on the island)

466
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,800
(Easy peasy, lemon squeezy)

467
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:51,430
Han.

468
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,880
(Get some luck)
Please, I wanna go off the island.

469
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:55,880
You may have...

470
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:56,920
Like, Group 1 and Group 2.

471
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:57,680
Just like last time.

472
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:01,350
Getting up.

473
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:03,190
Let's go.

474
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,070
It's fine, let's go.

475
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:16,490
Perfect.

476
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:17,670
I can go to the hospital with you.

477
00:22:17,950 --> 00:22:18,950
You wanna come with me?

478
00:22:18,950 --> 00:22:19,590
Yeah.

479
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:21,110
This counts as a date, huh?

480
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,110
I think it does.

481
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:23,040
(Xuan Cheng needs
another hospital check-up)

482
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,430
I could go on a date every day.

483
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:25,280
Did you notice?

484
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:27,800
Does the hospital count as a date?

485
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,110
You haven't eaten yet?

486
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:36,000
I had just a little.

487
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:39,110
You've worked hard.

488
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:40,920
I said you've worked hard.

489
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:42,070
Why would I be working hard?

490
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,710
Because you just played that game.

491
00:22:44,710 --> 00:22:46,160
I didn't play that round very well.

492
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,710
Yesterday I noticed
you look good in the beanie.

493
00:22:55,970 --> 00:22:57,040
I went all in on you yesterday

494
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,800
probably because of that beanie.

495
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:01,350
You look well-behaved with a hat on.

496
00:23:02,190 --> 00:23:04,070
I love that well-behaved vibe.

497
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:05,760
I've always been well-behaved.

498
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:07,560
I'm a well-behaved baby.

499
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:10,160
Are you a well-behaved baby?

500
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,430
Of course I am.

501
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,560
I wonder if dating you

502
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,760
would feel like a mom
taking care of her son.

503
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:19,950
More like a dad with his daughter.

504
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:25,590
Are you really 34 or just 24?

505
00:23:25,590 --> 00:23:29,300
(Spine Surgery; Bone and Joint Surgery)

506
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:31,710
This part.

507
00:23:33,190 --> 00:23:34,590
This area's okay.

508
00:23:34,590 --> 00:23:35,760
Right here, it should be here.

509
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,350
You can move it like this?

510
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:38,590
It's fine.

511
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:42,710
See the fracture
runs all the way from here to here.

512
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:43,680
Here.

513
00:23:43,830 --> 00:23:44,830
(Bone fracture)
Right here.

514
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:46,040
Yes, exactly this spot.

515
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:47,830
You're lucky it's not bad.

516
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:48,470
It'll heal.

517
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,560
It's just a small crack.

518
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,680
If it splits open...

519
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:52,470
If it splits open more,
you'll need surgery.

520
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:53,640
Got it?

521
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,160
So I can't keep doing this all the time.

522
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:56,280
Don't move, okay?

523
00:23:57,410 --> 00:23:58,160
Put on a plaster cast.

524
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,230
It's nothing serious,

525
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:00,350
just keep it...

526
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:00,950
A cast.

527
00:24:00,950 --> 00:24:02,310
I'm scared I won't be able

528
00:24:02,310 --> 00:24:03,280
to use this hand.

529
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:04,710
How am I gonna get dressed?

530
00:24:04,710 --> 00:24:05,520
Just don't use it.

531
00:24:06,190 --> 00:24:06,760
No cast.

532
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:07,950
We'll just use something

533
00:24:07,950 --> 00:24:08,800
to fix it in place.

534
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,950
Then, let's go with a brace.

535
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:10,800
Okay, use the brace.

536
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:11,350
A brace.

537
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,190
It's not a big deal.

538
00:24:12,190 --> 00:24:12,920
Don't move too much.

539
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:13,590
Okay.

540
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:14,710
Alright.

541
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:15,800
Here's your paperwork.

542
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,640
Thanks.

543
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,430
Okay, thanks.

544
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:20,830
Don't make it too tight.

545
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:22,070
It hurts if it's tight.

546
00:24:23,310 --> 00:24:25,190
I'm such a bad guy.

547
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,190
Yeah, how am I gonna eat?

548
00:24:28,190 --> 00:24:29,230
I'll feed you, okay?

549
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,800
Only you can feed me.

550
00:24:31,220 --> 00:24:32,110
How else am I gonna eat?

551
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,000
I'll feed you.

552
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,070
Let me try first.

553
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:35,350
Eat like this.

554
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:38,760
Stop moving.

555
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,070
If you feed me,

556
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:42,190
then for now,

557
00:24:42,190 --> 00:24:44,000
we're like "mom" and "son".

558
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:47,920
Lean on me.

559
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:48,430
Sure.

560
00:24:48,430 --> 00:24:48,830
Lean on me.

561
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:49,470
I put my head here.

562
00:24:49,470 --> 00:24:50,760
No, I mean on my shoulder.

563
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:51,640
Lean on your shoulder.

564
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,310
I kinda like it
when a man leans on my shoulder.

565
00:24:55,190 --> 00:24:56,070
Gotta press this in.

566
00:24:57,170 --> 00:24:57,980
Like this?

567
00:24:57,980 --> 00:24:58,480
Does it hurt?

568
00:24:58,480 --> 00:24:59,230
No.

569
00:25:02,110 --> 00:25:04,040
Having Jiayi with me
at the hospital today

570
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:06,560
made me see a different side of her.

